A minimalistic Japanese zen garden viewed from above, featuring carefully raked white sand with precise parallel lines forming geometric patterns, a single dark polished stone positioned off-center, and one small bonsai tree casting a subtle shadow. The composition emphasizes negative space and balance, with soft natural daylight creating gentle gradients across the sand. The color palette is muted with cream whites, soft grays, and one touch of deep green from the bonsai. The raked sand patterns flow around the stone like water, suggesting organized data flowing through categories. Clean, serene, contemplative atmosphere with sharp edges meeting organic curves.
